<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The type for the operand information call back function.  This is called to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; get the symbolic information for an operand of an instruction.  Typically</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; this is from the relocation information, symbol table, etc.  That block of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; information is saved when the disassembler context is created and passed to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the call back in the DisInfo parameter.  The instruction containing operand</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; is at the PC parameter.  For some instruction sets, there can be more than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; one operand with symbolic information.  To determine the symbolic operand</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; information for each operand, the bytes for the specific operand in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; instruction are specified by the Offset parameter and its byte widith is the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; OpSize parameter.  For instructions sets with fixed widths and one symbolic</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; operand per instruction, the Offset parameter will be zero and InstSize</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; parameter will be the instruction width.  The information is returned in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; TagBuf and is Triple specific with its specific information defined by the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; value of TagType for that Triple.  If symbolic information is returned the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; function &#42; returns 1, otherwise it returns 0</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48" lineLink="/docs/api/groups/llvmcdisassembler/#gaa8eb7ea1e53fd6e7a11b6aa4749c6e60"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typedef</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> int (&#42;<a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmcdisassembler/#gaa8eb7ea1e53fd6e7a11b6aa4749c6e60">LLVMOpInfoCallback</a>)(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;DisInfo, uint64&#95;t PC, uint64&#95;t Offset,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="normal">                                  uint64&#95;t OpSize, uint64&#95;t InstSize,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="normal">                                  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> TagType, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;TagBuf);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The initial support in LLVM MC for the most general form of a relocatable</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; expression is &quot;AddSymbol - SubtractSymbol + Offset&quot;.  For some Darwin targets</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; this full form is encoded in the relocation information so that AddSymbol and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; SubtractSymbol can be link edited independent of each other.  Many other</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; platforms only allow a relocatable expression of the form AddSymbol + Offset</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; to be encoded.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The LLVMOpInfoCallback() for the TagType value of 1 uses the struct</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; LLVMOpInfo1.  The value of the relocatable expression for the operand,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; including any PC adjustment, is passed in to the call back in the Value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; field.  The symbolic information about the operand is returned using all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; the fields of the structure with the Offset of the relocatable expression</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; returned in the Value field.  It is possible that some symbols in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; relocatable expression were assembly temporary symbols, for example</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; &quot;Ldata - LpicBase + constant&quot;, and only the Values of the symbols without</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; symbol names are present in the relocation information.  The VariantKind</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; type is one of the Target specific #defines below and is used to print</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; operands like &quot;&#95;foo@GOT&quot;, &quot;:lower16:&#95;foo&quot;, etc.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; offset load instruction to use a symbol name instead of a load address value.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; It is passed the block information is saved when the disassembler context is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="111"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; created and the ReferenceValue to look up as a symbol.  If no symbol is found</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="112"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; for the ReferenceValue NULL is returned.  The ReferenceType of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="113"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; instruction is passed indirectly as is the PC of the instruction in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="114"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; ReferencePC.  If the output reference can be determined its type is returned</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="115"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; indirectly in ReferenceType along with ReferenceName if any, or that is set</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="116"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; to NULL.</Highlight></CodeLine>
